## 🎯 MASTER INTERVIEW CHEAT SHEET

### "Tell me about this project" (60-second pitch)
*"CodeWeave is a production-grade, real-time collaborative code editor — think Google Docs but for code. I built it full-stack with React, Node.js, and MongoDB. The core collaboration uses Yjs CRDTs, which mathematically guarantee that any number of users can type simultaneously without conflicts. I integrated Monaco Editor — the same engine as VS Code — for a professional editing experience. Users can execute code in JavaScript, Python, C++, and Java through the Judge0 CE API, which provides a sandboxed execution environment. I secured the platform with Clerk authentication, giving users a persistent dashboard of their workspaces. The backend follows strict MVC architecture with a service layer, and I overcame some significant infrastructure challenges including a Docker cgroup v2 incompatibility and a Node.js-specific DNS resolution bug."*

### Key Differentiating Talking Points
| Topic | Your Edge |
|---|---|
| **CRDTs vs OT** | Can explain the mathematical difference; CRDTs don't need a central server to resolve conflicts |
| **Debouncing writes** | Reduced DB writes by 99%+ — shows awareness of production constraints |
| **cgroup v2 bug** | Deep systems debugging — port-level diagnosis, kernel-level root cause |
| **DNS hijacking fix** | Node.js internals (`c-ares`) — most candidates have never seen this |
| **Server-side Yjs hooks** | Server is the source of truth, not the client — proper distributed system design |
| **MVC + Service layer** | Clean architecture beyond just "MVC" — external API abstraction |
| **Base64 for code payloads** | Knows WHY, not just how — binary-safe serialization rationale |
